[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **The problem:** The concepts of "static protocols can't adapt" and "this is a sequential decision problem" are stated twice with slightly different framing. The third paragraph ends with "The protocol is a lookup table. The problem demands a controller." The fourth paragraph then re-establishes the same point with the NICE-SUGAR discussion. This is minor; the NICE-SUGAR context adds value, but the transition could be tighter.
